README for caching server. This is intended to be a living document, to be
clear what the caching layer does and what not.

Caching static files is trivial. Synchronization is more of a problem, so
concentrating on caching activations makes sense, as they are anyway already
almost in a log format, making it also quickly realizable.


       +--------------------------+                         - optional Caching
       |      EasyLab Server      |                         - HTML5 offline APP
       |     (public IPv4+v6)     |                           (=> Mobile)
       +--------------------------+

 +------------------------------------------------------+
 |                      Lab LAN                         |
 |                                                      |
 |  +------------------------------------------------+  |   +-----------------+
 |  |               EasyLab Cache                    |  |   |    Switch 1     |
 |  |                                                |  |   |  (public IPv6)  |
 |  |  +-------------------+   +------------------+  |  |   +-----------------+
 |  |  |   Fallback for    |   |  Forward proxy   |  |  |
 |  |  | /api/activations  |   | for easylab.io   |  |  |   +-----------------+
 |  |  |                   |   | cache manifest & |  |  |   |    Switch ...   |
 |  |  | (sync w/ web svc) |   | related files    |  |  |   |  (public IPv6)  |
 |  |  +-------------------+   +------------------+  |  |   +-----------------+
 |  |                                                |  |
 |  +------------------------------------------------+  |
 |                                                      |
 |            +------------------------+                |
 |            |     Browser Client     |                |  +------------------+
 |            |         Lab LAN        |                |  | Browser Client   |
 |            +------------------------+                |  |     Internet     |
 |                                                      |  +------------------+
 |                                                      |
 +------------------------------------------------------+
